description:
Reiser  is  kidnapped  by the  revolutionary group  "Vox  World"  that is threatening  to kill him .  
Meanwhile ,  Solomon  Darver   isolate and evacuate the   "Alfa Agency" Building , Nathan  and his fellow  reveal the illegal activities  of their  leader.  
After  discovering the  nature of their new  exoskeletons ,  in  reality  clones  of  Nathan ,  Legs ,  May ,  April  and  Jack  O'Ryan , the Alfa Agents  go  in the office  of  Sigmund , where  the  Polish  reveals  the truth  about  the  birth of The Agency.
name: Il Patto

description:
Professor Odaka did not abandon his mad project to restore the pre-history on Earth , this time , with the complicity of Mr. Alfa , uses the mysterious pylons of Atlantis , machines capable of creating an anomaly in time.
Nathan , Legs and Branko , with the help of the woman- beast Ran , traveling to the area where the pylons are at work and run into Zemira , of the lineage of the Venerable
name: I Signori della preistoria

description:
The ex boxer Larry " Brutus " Powell , a giant with a heart of gold , is wrongly accused of murdering the young Felicia Kerry .
Mickey Walls , ex coach of Brutus , hires " Nathan Never " in order to clear him, to prove its innocence he will deal a serious blow to the promising career of Judge Nicholas Dewey and his protected Debra Stone .
To avoid this , Nicholas and Debra will attempt to silence the real culprit before you find Nathan .
name: L'anima della città

description: The first part of Neal Adams's Batman epic comes to a dramatic conclusion as Batman, Deadman and The Joker – working together and against each other – break into Arkham Asylum and confront the doctors who control the most heinous criminals. But does some other powerful individual control these monsters? Is it the Sensei, the deadliest martial artist in the world and leader of the League of Assassins? Or is it Ra's al Ghul, the greatest opponent Batman has ever faced? And is The Dark Knight willing to let Talia die to bring this monstrous clash to an end?
name: Part 6

description:
In the town of Mescal ,at  the borders of the Territory , Raul Corben is the absolute master (Among his henchmen there is also , Sakova , head of the local police station ! ) .
In its construction sites, using hundreds of illegal immigrants as workers , treated like slaves .
But all this is destined to end  , at least according to the predictions of the sensory Keira .
Nathan meanwhile , meets the young Lena , an illegal managed to escape , and he begins to investigate .
name: Il territorio

description: Special POINT ONE issue. START READING with this Point One issue. Tony Stark takes his first steps into the future! The Armored Avenger soars to never before seen heights and he's not going alone. Learn what it means to be Iron Man in the 21st Century! This issue sets the stage for the most action packed story in ol' Shellhead's life!
name: What It Was Like, What Happened, And What It's Like Now

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

description:
Overview

A Marvel Masterpiece from deep inside the treasure vaults can now be told! For decades, Doctor Stephen Strange has worked as a practicing sorcerer out of the weird old brownstone at 177A Bleecker Street in Manhattan's Greenwich Village. But what eerie secrets does the building hide? What lurks within its walls? Is it … haunted? Now, at last, the full story of Doctor Strange's first night in his Sanctum Sanctorum stands revealed –- in a tale tastefully told by Roger Stern (AMAZING SPIDER-MAN) and dramatically drawn by those Masters of the Comic Arts, Neil Vokes and Jay Geldhof (UNTOLD TALES OF SPIDER-MAN: STRANGE ENCOUNTERS, The Black Forest).

Dedicated to the masters, Stan Lee and Steve Ditko.
name: This Old House

volume.name: Doctor Strange: From the Marvel Vault

description: Kick-Ass 2 continues to, well, Kick-Ass, and the Turf wars reach their spectacular conclusion this issue! Meanwhile, the world of Rex Royd continues its plunging descent into the surreal. All this plus a host of new, never-before-seen brilliance from a host of new talent, groomed for the top slot by Mark Millar himself!

Featuring Witchblade, The Darkness, Angelus, Magdalena, Cyberforce, Hunter-Killer and other Top Cow Universe favorites! When a distraught mother surrenders her baby at a New York City fire station during a winter snowstorm, Sara Pezzini, Jackie Estacado, the Hunter-Killers, and other Top Cow Universe characters find themselves pulled together in the spirit of the holidays to aid the innocent newborn. What quickly becomes apparent is there are larger sinister forces at play here with the baby as the focal point of a supernatural event that will take Top Cow greatest heroes banding together to save, not only a city, but a single child as well. Includes Paul Dini's Jingle Belle: Grounded.

In this flip book special, the heroes of the Top Cow universe team up during a crisis revolving around a abandoned baby. Alternately, this issue features short stories involving Santa's daughter, Jingle.

volume.name: Top Cow Holiday Special/Jingle Belle Grounded

description: THE ILLUMINATI versus THE PRIDE as "INDUSTRIAL REVOLUTION" reaches its senses-shattering conclusion!
name: Industrial Revolution Part 6

description: SPINNING FROM THE AMAZING SPIDER-MAN! The greatest secret Spider-Girl has is her secret identity. Her secret protects both her and the lives of her friends and loved ones. Anya Corazon makes a fateful decision to share that secret with someone…but what are the consequences, and why has the RED HULK come for a rematch against Spider-Girl?
name: A Certain Point Of View

description:
The Security Council entrusts the  Alfa Agency  to checking  the safety systems of the Yakama , a private company that will take care to dismantle some nuclear warheads that are coveted by several revolutionary groups for the independence of the Colonies .
Among the probably interested in their warheads , there is also the gang of Sammy Walken , who has just hired the young Tony Ivers .
name: L'infiltrato

description:
Overview:
 
By Jodorowsky, Travis Charest, Moebius, and Juan Gimenez. Travis Charest, Juan Gimenez, and Moebius all come together in this must-have Metabarons special! Metabarons: Alpha/Omega is a celebration of the series' past, as well as a look into its future. Featuring short stories as well as missing pages from Incal and Metabarons, all written by Metabarons creator, Alexandro Jodorowsky, Alpha/Omega is an important history lesson for any fan, new or old. This is the first-ever published Metabarons material by Travis Charest, in a story that leads into his upcoming projects featuring the characters. Also appearing in the story, "The Crest of the Castaka," by Jodorowsky and Gimenez, tells the origin of the tattoo that adorns the chest of every Metabaron, as well as pages by Moebius and Gimenez that have never seen print in America. Metabarons: Alpha/Omega is the perfect place for new Metabarons fans to see why the series has gained such critical acclaim from creators such as Warren Ellis. And Travis Charest fans are sure to turn out en masse to see what is sure to be some of the best work in his already illustrious career.
name: Metabarons Alpha/Omega

description: Yoshinori, dressed as Yuki, hears Hidari confess that she is actually in love with him. Hearing his childhood friend confess her feelings for him, he is emotionally shaken.
name: Vol. 1

description: As his body continues to go through changes, Yoshinuri decides that he can't continue cross-dressing. Now with "Yuki" gone, who can he get to model at the photography studio? Hidari? Kurokawa? But as Yoshinori's plans to stop cross-dressing come to a halt, Kurokawa begs him to continue. She is only able to open up to him when he is dressed as a girl, but during one of their outings, Yoshinori's best friend Wataru sees him dressed as Yuki, and it's love at first sight. Meanwhile, Hidari will do anything to get Yoshinori to see her as more than a little kid.
name: Vol. 2

description: Yoshinori can't decide on who he has a crush on- Minamo or Hidari. Seems like Yoshinori will never be able to muster up the courage to tell Hidari how he feels about her. He better think of something quick because Yuki seems to be getting very close to Hidari. Wait, Yoshinori is Yuki! Sounds like a weird love triangle is being drawn...
name: Vol. 3

description: It's off to the hot springs for the Ikeda and Morii families! Hidari takes the opportunity to seduce Yoshinori by going to his room and stripping! How will Yoshinori react? Meanwhile, Miki has set her sights on Hidari's father, Yusuke...what will happen between those two?! Then there's drama on the soccer field as Minamo watches Yuki become very friendly with both Wataru and Nobuko! Is Minamo's close relationship with Yoshinori in danger?
name: Vol. 4

description: Something always seems to come between two people in a budding romance, and for Yoshinori, that something turns out to be his sister Miki! As Yoshinori's passion for Minamo grows--while his feelings fade for Hidari--he plans a romantic birthday dinner for her. This is his chance to show Minamo what's truly in his heart arises...but the only thing that can stop him now is an overzealous Miki!
name: Vol. 5

description: Inspired by Minamo's femininity, Yoshinori finds himself drunk on the power of his convincing female form. As if being in love with Hidari and Minamo weren't enough, Yoshinori puts his cross-dressing abilities to the test when he goes on a date with Wataru--as Yuki! But in spite of all those that love him, will Yoshinaro discover that he is actually most in love with...Yuki?
name: Vol. 6

description: When Yoshinori fills in for his sister as a bridal gown model, he discovers he actually likes to crossdress! And so a whole new world opens up for him--as a she! Yoshinori discovers that he still has a lot to learn about love as his careless words may cost him Minamo's affections forever. Will this give Hidari the chance she's been waiting for? Or will Yoshinori be forced to do the unthinkable in order to win Minamo back--give up his cross-dressing as Yuki?
name: Vol. 7

description: When Yoshinori dresses like Yuki to go out on a date with Wataru, they run into trouble and Wataru ends up with an injured leg. Will this threaten his soccer career in high school? And when he finds out Yuki’s true identify, will their relationship be ruined forever? Nogi from the basketball club is having trouble keeping control of her team, and Yoshinori’s seductive administrations might just do the trick to get her out of her funk.
name: Vol. 8

Meet Armand Jones--a typical boy from small-town U.S.A. Doesn't like his teachers. Doesn't like homework. Can't stand the bullies constantly harassing him on the bus every day. But what he really won't like is getting Zapt! Armand is about to be inducted into the ranks of the Pan-Galactic Order of Police, where, like it or not, he'll have to save alien races and outwit marauding space pirates! And he'll still have to be home in time for dinner. Being a kid is about to get a lot harder!
name: Zapt!

description: Since being inducted into the ranks of P.O.O.P (Pan-galactic Order Of Police), 12-year-old Armand Jones has had more trouble keeping out of detention at school than he has with capturing alien outlaws. But now, there's major turmoil spreading across the galaxy, and it's got Mr. Big, Red and Ugly's fingerprints all over it!
name: Gongar's Revenge

description: Since defeating Gongar and his hordes in a battle that cost them their headquarters, the P.O.O.P. Ops scour the universe looking for the fiend. But when Gongar finally does turn up, it's with a devious plan to legally take over one of the most powerful planets in the galaxy! Now it's up to Armand to save the day, and make it to the school dance... hopefully, alive!
name: Royal Blood

In a private school only recently open to girls, flower-lovin' Takaaki is a breath of fresh (and gender-blurred) air! Having to room with the stone cold Sonoh Takahara has certainly caused him some angst, but don't fear. Sonoh's twin is his complete opposite, making for a whole mess of fun filled with cute boys and silly misunderstandings.

Back Blurb

In a private school only recently open to girls, flower-lovin' Takaaki is a breath of fresh air! Sure he's short, cute and often mistaken for a girl. He's also really into plants and flowers, mostly due to his secret crush, Marika. When Takaaki moves into his new dormitory, he and his mysterious, distant roommate Sonoh seem like complete opposites at first. But the two begin to discover that they have more in common than they first thought---and Takaaki embarks on a journey to find out just who is the real Sonoh!

Chapter 1 to 4.

Meanwhile, Saho starts to realize just how much she likes Taiyou, even though Taiyou is still stuck on Marika. Are they on a collision course with heartbreak?

Taiyou and Sonoh, with the help of a sadistic classmate, are out for revenge against the bullying scare tactics of resident assistant Jinjin. 13-year-old Lili is just like any other girl, except she can foretell the future! When she transforms into her alter-ego, Detective Spica, this 'Zodiac P.I.' relies on horoscopes and astrology to help her solve crimes and track down criminals. When her classmate, Chihiro Seto, is murdered, it's up to the Zodiac P.I. to solve the case. With a little help from her friend Hiromi, she vows to track down the killer. When she suspects one of her own teachers is to blame, Lili must follow her instincts...and the stars, until she finds the truth. Once that case is behind her, Detective Spica receives an anonymous letter alerting her to the presence of a ghost in a nearby piano school. When she goes undercover as a piano student to investigate, she stumbles upon a bloody crime scene and finds herself investigating yet another murder. Will the Zodiac P.I. be able to unravel this mystery before the killer strikes again?!
name: Vol. 1

description: Lili is flooded with cases involving people who are near and dear to her; nevertheless, she somehow manages to go on with her life. But, her appearance on an astrology-themed TV show may lead her into uncharted--and dangerous--territory when an astrologist is poisoned. It's her first high profile case and it's up to Lili to prove her mettle in the court of public opinion!
name: Vol. 2

description: Lili and her partner Hiromi journey to Kyoto on their vacation...and end up with much more than they bargained for! Then, a series of love letters ends up causing some serious havoc until their origin and purpose is eventually revealed...by the Zodiac P.I., of course!
name: Vol. 3

description: Lili and Hiromi visit a mysterious fortune-teller called Zeus...and find themselves, along with Lili's father, embroiled in a situation in which the fate of the Star Ring itself is very much in doubt...
name: Vol. 4

Tamayo Akiyama, a former member of CLAMP, has crafted an unforgettable shojo adventure that will leave readers spellbound! Welcome to Zyword, a world filled with magic and sorcery. When Zyword's kingdom of Araimel is put under a spell, it's up to two survivors to save everyone from an eternal sleep!

  • Luna's Reminiscence
  • Araimel Newsletter
  • Araimel Newsletter Extra

description: Mikan and her friends are 6th graders now, but the new school year is starting off on an uncomfortable foot. The school president introduces the newly created Public Morals Squad during the opening ceremony, and it's pretty clear whose behavior they will be keeping the closest eye on. To top it off, there's a new student in Mikan's class! Welcome, Luna Koizumi! But for an apparently gentle girl with a sickly demeanor, she seems like she's up to something...

The Alice Academy’s Spring Sports Festival is intensifying and the students can feel the electricity! A scavenger hunt gives Natsume a chance to express his feelings in a truly surprising way, but Mikan is in even more danger as Luna’s sway over the student body grows. As the threats on her life increase, can Natsume give Mikan the strength to go on, or will his actions push her to the breaking point?
name: Vol. 15

description:
Final exams are almost over at Aitan Gakuen, but will Yuuki pass the last test - a game of hide-and-seek? After the commotion, summer vacation finds Yuuki spending time at the Monkey Clan home at Sawa’s invitation. Yuuki learns more about himself and his companions, but is something suspicious going on? And is Sawa hiding something?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 16: Reverse Hide-and-Seek, Part 1
  • Chapter 17: Reverse Hide-and-Seek, Part 2
  • Chapter 18: Reverse Hide-and-Seek, Part 3
  • Chapter 19: Return to the Monkey House, Part 1
  • Chapter 20: Return to the Monkey House, Part 2
  • Bonus Chapter: The Promise of a Peach Garden

description: Aso has crossed the divide between human and allegory. As his battle with Kitou Kokkuri rages on, Hanako and Kanae try to come up with a way to return him to normal. Can they do it before he turns on them? The mysteries continue to swirl ever faster around the Aso Detective Agency in this chilling volume of Hanako and the Terror of Allegory!
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: Hanako and the Terror of Allegory

description: When Shuto is knocked unconscious during his battle with the hero Ankaiser, Ratman’s innate abilities take over and pummel his opponent. During recovery later, Shuto is wracked with doubt over his new heroic role. When it seems that his idyllic view of the world of heroism was just an illusion, what’s a would-be super hero to do?
name: Vol. 3

description: World War what? It’s all about getting to know each other (or at least trying to) in this hilarious second volume of Hetalia Axis Powers! And with the Hetalia Academy, tons of new character introductions along with preparing for the Olympics, there’s no time left for the battlefield! But leave it to Italy’s ancestor, “that jerk” England, and pushy America to stir things up while good old Canada, quiet Japan and sweet little Liechtenstein respectfully go about their day. Isn’t it about time they all started getting along? [new paragraph] Find out what all the commotion is about in this witty second volume that offers more of the historical and peculiar storytelling that placed Hetalia at the Number One spot on the New York Times Manga Bestseller list.
name: Vol. 2

description: Should their past lives determine what happens in the present? Keidai and Mii were best buds in Pompeii, but all that's changed now that Mii's a girl! After Mii confesses her feelings for him at the amusement center, Keidai rethinks their complicated relationship. But when a childhood friend of Mii's transfers back to their high school, Keidai needs to come to terms with his feelings before he loses her forever!
name: Vol. 7

description: Keidai accepts his love for Mii, but when he decides to confess his feelings to her, he finds himself forgetting everything about their past lives in Pompeii! Will Keidai give up his past to embrace a happy future with Mii, just as key memories of their past lives, including their final days in the doomed city and the betrayal of Aglaia, reveal themselves?
name: Vol. 8

description:
Mermaids and mind-controlling parasites wage war in this much anticipated series from the creator of CHIBI VAMPIRE! Tatsuya Tsugawa has just lost both of his parents in a car accident. While trying to live up to his father's dying wish of becoming an upstanding man, Tatsuya rushes to help Seine--his bizarre classmate--from bullies. Little does he know he is about to find himself in the middle of a supernatural war between the immortal Seine and sea creatures that can control humans. So much for being Mr. Nice Guy!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter #1: Little Man
  • Chapter #2: Small Fry
  • Chapter #3: Homeless Girl
  • Chapter #4: Family Reversal
name: Vol. 1

description: After Jin accidentally returns to the human world before completing his test, Kanoto volunteers everyone to help out. Is Jin willing to risk everyone’s lives just to pass the test? Meanwhile, Kogane is struggling with her studies so Jin offers to tutor her, but will it be enough when faced with a major distraction? And if that wasn’t too much drama, Kogane and Sogo are getting pretty close and go on a date! Will this lead to love?
name: Vol. 3

description:
Winter has arrived in Neo-Venezia, and Akari, Aika and Alicia go back to Aria Company to find Athena visiting Alicia. Alicia reminisces about the time when she, Akira and Athena were practice buddies. Now, Athena says they all have become too busy to see each other after they got promoted to Prima and Alice somberly comments that their days of rowing practice may come to an end...

Kazuya is just getting settled into his new role as one of the Gaarts, but the evil organization BURN is out to conquer the world with... a sports festival? When BURN kidnaps Kazuya, it's up to Hina and the rest of the girls to save him. If they can stop getting in each others way first! And what's this about Kazuya's long-lost fiancee? The drama in this house is getting out of control!

description:
Determined to bring his deadbeat father to justice for the death of his mother, Yukiteru tracks down his father only to meet with a sickening surprise! Meanwhile, the Eleventh diary owner finally makes his move to seize Eighth's special server diary for his own purposes. Yukiteru's plan to strike back and take both down at once is foiled when Aru Akise returns with a shocking piece of information about Yuno's true identity!

Vol. 9

description: Yuri is more confused then ever when confronted with a mysterious girl confessing to Hirao--that can’t take No for an answer. Isn’t she still stuck on Yabe? This might just be the push needed for Hirao to get a real date with Yuri. More is going on then what it seems and the gang must act quickly to stop the impending danger targeting the couple!
name: Vol. 8

description: Mona and Rina have a new housemate--K2, a demon who looks exactly like their idol Keito! When Mona and Rina are presented with a chance to meet Keito, they have to do everything they can to keep K2 from following them! But their seemingly tranquil life is suddenly threatened with the appearance of another demon--Griffin. Will K2's help be enough to save Mona from being consumed by Griffin?
name: Vol. 2

description: Trouble abounds when Keito finds out about the existence of K2 and decides to make a home visit, but he isn’t the only one knocking on their door--demons target Mona and Rina in a devious plan hatched by the Griffin. The girls aren’t the only ones with troubles as Helmut comes to Japan to prepare for X-day to unveil SMIC and make the information about the demons public, along with his deadly countermeasures!
name: Vol. 3

description: As she faces new challenges, Odette must learn the value of self-respect, what it means to truly sympathize with others, and why her unusual family is more important than a cell phone. And when Odette meets a fellow android named Travis, her journey of self-discovery takes a surprising turn!
name: Vol. 5
